node.text: We have settled for the term “police brutality”in America. The term police brutality does not fit George Floyd as we watched his Civil Rights being violated !!! Policing units and individuals have terrorized black people dating back to slave patrols and into the present . The fear instated into the black and minority community is intentional always has been! I realize for some Americans this statement is simply not true and I am glad you have that PRIVILEGED viewpoint but others such as George Floyd and countless other human beings that we don’t know, it is a different reality.. Reminder it’s 2020 and the Ku Klux Klan is not classified as a terrorist organization it’s 2020 and lynching is STILL not a federal hate crime !! People yell in the comments all the time “racism doesn’t exist” and I can finally understand that racism is so deep and normalized they can’t even see it ! So I guess in a sick way they gotta point

node.text: Slavery and or racism is apart of America’s history but it does not have to be apart of the present or future.. Francis Scott Key was a slave owner and mentioned embracing slavery in the 3rd verse of the national anthem google it .. I respect what others have done on different soils for me to be an American however it’s threats on our own soil and we continue to ignore them !! 1812 was a different time than it is now I understand that, but I disagree that I should embrace that time period, that time period did not embrace me.. I respect your decision if you still choose to stand, to each is own

node.text: You did it bro this the moment we all were waiting on all the hard work sleepless nights moments of doubt the family is proud of you !! You left your mark all over the world I’m blessed to have shared these moments with you .. love is forever 💚 the whole fam misses you Gavin and I was talking about you the other day we got your back 💯 WE ARE SO PROUD OF YOU !! You did your thing kid p.s I appreciate you letting me get my lil vet tricks off lol love you bro 💚 #LLTC5
